   "id": "19d675f5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "RAG stands for Retrieval-Augmented Generation. It's an AI technique that combines the strengths of retrieval systems and language models to enhance the performance of natural language processing tasks. Here’s how it works:\n",
      "\n",
      "1. **Retrieval**: The system retrieves relevant documents or information from a large corpus of data.\n",
      "\n",
      "2. **Augmentation**: The retrieved information is then used as additional context for generating answers. This context can help improve the accuracy and relevance of the generated output by providing more comprehensive information than a traditional language model alone would have access to.\n",
      "\n",
      "3. **Generation**: Using the combined information, a language model generates an answer to the given question.\n",
      "\n",
      "RAG aims to provide high-quality responses by leveraging both the efficiency of retrieval systems and the flexibility and depth of natural language models. This approach can be particularly useful in scenarios where large datasets are available but traditional machine learning models might not perform well due to lack of data or complexity.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "response = llm.invoke(\"What is RAG\")\n",
    "print(response.content)"
   ]
  },
